1. Turn off kth bit in a number

    Web answer is n & ~(1 << k- 1).

    For me: n ^ (1 << (k - 1)) will also work

2. Turn on kth bit in a number.

    n | (1 << k- 1) will do

3. Check if k'th bit is set for a number.

    (1 << (k - 1))  will help here

4. Toggle the kth bit

    (1 << (k - 1))  will help here